cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. 

This paper is about distant supervision and neural relation extraction, which are both topics in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a neural pattern diagnosis framework, which involves training a neural network, so it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed framework in improving the accuracy of relation extraction, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses real-world datasets, which could suggest a focus on practical applications, making it relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
